{
  "text": "The commonest way to describe associations of cyclic limb movements is plotting their inter-limb phase relations. From this material such relations were easily obtained as the differences between the clk-mov curves of the hand and foot for each of the various loading and coupling combinations. These interlimb relations are shown in Fig. 6 for isodirectional (A) and antidirectional (B) oscillations, with different symbols for the three loading conditions (black squares: both segments unloaded; blue diamonds: hand loaded, red diamonds: foot loaded). The illustrated relations confirm the previously described delaying effects of inertial loading on the hand curves [CITATION_1] and add the description of the effects of foot loading on the curves.",
